  27,1,ŠĻ¨√Ę-Sń©n. These are the verses of the Quran; the clear Book
  27,2,ňĻIt isňļ a guide and good news for the believers
  27,3,"ňĻthoseňļ who establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and have sure faith in the Hereafter"
  27,4,"As for those who do not believe in the Hereafter, We have certainly made their ňĻevilňļ deeds appealing to them, so they wander blindly"
  27,5,"It is they who will suffer a dreadful torment, and in the Hereafter they will ňĻtrulyňļ be the greatest losers"
  27,6,"And indeed, you ňĻO Prophetňļ are receiving the Quran from the One ňĻWho isňļ All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  27,7,"ňĻRememberňļ when Moses said to his family, ‚ÄúI have spotted a fire. I will either bring you some directions¬†from there, or a burning torch so you may warm yourselves.‚ÄĚ"
  27,8,"But when he came to it, he was called ňĻby Allahňļ, ‚ÄúBlessed is the one at the fire, and whoever is around it!¬†Glory be to Allah, the Lord of all worlds"
  27,9,"O Moses! It is truly I. I am Allah‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  27,10,"Now, throw down your staff!‚ÄĚ But when he saw it slithering like a snake, he ran away without looking back. ňĻAllah reassured him,ňļ ‚ÄúO Moses! Do not be afraid! Messengers should have no fear in My presence"
  27,11,"ňĻFear isňļ only for those who do wrong. But if they later mend ňĻtheirňļ evil ňĻwaysňļ with good, then I am certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  27,12,"Now put your hand through ňĻthe opening ofňļ your collar, it will come out ňĻshiningňļ white, unblemished.¬†ňĻThese are twoňļ of nine signs for Pharaoh and his people.¬†They have truly been a rebellious people.‚ÄĚ"
  27,13,"But when Our enlightening signs came to them, they said, ‚ÄúThis is pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  27,14,"And, although their hearts were convinced the signs were true, they still denied them wrongfully and arrogantly. See then what was the end of the corruptors"
  27,15,"Indeed, We granted knowledge to David and Solomon. And they said ňĻin acknowledgmentňļ, ‚ÄúAll praise is for Allah Who has privileged us over many of His faithful servants.‚ÄĚ"
  27,16,"And David was succeeded by Solomon, who said, ‚ÄúO people! We have been taught the language of birds, and been given everything ňĻwe needňļ. This is indeed a great privilege.‚ÄĚ"
  27,17,"Solomon‚Äôs forces of jinn, humans, and birds were rallied for him, perfectly organized"
  27,18,"And when they came across a valley of ants, an ant warned, ‚ÄúO ants! Go quickly into your homes so Solomon and his armies do not crush you, unknowingly.‚ÄĚ"
  27,19,"So Solomon smiled in amusement at her words, and prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Inspire me to ňĻalwaysňļ be thankful for Your favours which You have blessed me and my parents with, and to do good deeds that please you. Admit me, by Your mercy, into ňĻthe company ofňļ Your righteous servants.‚ÄĚ"
  27,20,"ňĻOne dayňļ he inspected the birds, and wondered, ‚ÄúWhy is it that I cannot see the hoopoe? Or could he be absent"
  27,21,"I will surely subject him to a severe punishment, or ňĻevenňļ slaughter him, unless he brings me a compelling excuse.‚ÄĚ"
  27,22,"It was not long before the bird came and said, ‚ÄúI have found out something you do not know. I have just come to you from Sheba with sure news"
  27,23,"Indeed, I found a woman ruling over them,¬†who has been given everything ňĻshe needsňļ, and who has a magnificent throne"
  27,24,I found her and her people prostrating to the sun instead of Allah. For Satan has made their deeds appealing to them‚ÄĒhindering them from the ňĻRightňļ Way and leaving them unguided‚ÄĒ
  27,25,"so they do not prostrate to Allah, Who brings forth what is hidden in the heavens and the earth, and knows what you ňĻallňļ conceal and what you reveal"
  27,26,"ňĻHe isňļ Allah! There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him, the Lord of the Mighty Throne.‚ÄĚ"
  27,27,"Solomon said, ‚ÄúWe will see whether you are telling the truth or lying"
  27,28,"Go with this letter of mine and deliver it to them, then stand aside and see how they will respond.‚ÄĚ"
  27,29,"The Queen ňĻlaterňļ announced, ‚ÄúO chiefs! Indeed, a noble letter has been delivered to me"
  27,30,"It is from Solomon, and it reads: ‚ÄėIn the Name of Allah‚ÄĒthe Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  27,31,"Do not be arrogant with me, but come to me, fully submitting ňĻto Allahňļ.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  27,32,"She said, ‚ÄúO chiefs! Advise me in this matter of mine, for I would never make any decision without you.‚ÄĚ"
  27,33,"They responded, ‚ÄúWe are a people of strength and great ňĻmilitaryňļ might, but the decision is yours, so decide what you will command.‚ÄĚ"
  27,34,"She reasoned, ‚ÄúIndeed, when kings invade a land, they ruin it and debase its nobles. They really do so"
  27,35,"But I will certainly send him a gift, and see what ňĻresponseňļ my envoys will return with.‚ÄĚ"
  27,36,"When the chief-envoy came to him, Solomon said, ‚ÄúDo you offer me wealth? What Allah has granted me is far greater than what He has granted you. No! It is you who rejoice in ňĻreceivingňļ gifts"
  27,37,"Go back to them, for we will certainly mobilize against them forces which they can never resist, and we will drive them out from there in disgrace, fully humbled.‚ÄĚ"
  27,38,"Solomon asked, ‚ÄúO chiefs! Which of you can bring me her throne before they come to me in ňĻfullňļ submission?‚ÄĚ"
  27,39,"One mighty jinn responded, ‚ÄúI can bring it to you before you rise from this council of yours. And I am quite strong and trustworthy for this ňĻtaskňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  27,40,"But the one who had knowledge of the Scripture said,¬†‚ÄúI can bring it to you in the blink of an eye.‚ÄĚ So when Solomon saw it placed before him, he exclaimed, ‚ÄúThis is by the grace of my Lord to test me whether I am grateful or ungrateful. And whoever is grateful, it is only for their own good. But whoever is ungrateful, surely my Lord is Self-Sufficient, Most Generous.‚ÄĚ"
  27,41,"ňĻThenňļ Solomon said, ‚ÄúDisguise her throne for her so we may see whether she will recognize ňĻitňļ or she will not be able to.‚ÄĚ"
  27,42,"So when she arrived, it was said ňĻto herňļ, ‚ÄúIs your throne like this?‚ÄĚ She replied, ‚ÄúIt looks to be the same. We have ňĻalreadyňļ received knowledge ňĻof Solomon‚Äôs prophethoodňļ¬†before this ňĻmiracleňļ,¬†and have submitted ňĻto Allahňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  27,43,"But she had been hindered by what she used to worship instead of Allah, for she was indeed from a disbelieving people"
  27,44,"Then she was told, ‚ÄúEnter the palace.‚ÄĚ But when she saw the hall, she thought it was a body of water, so she bared her legs. Solomon said. ‚ÄúIt is just a palace paved with crystal.‚ÄĚ ňĻAt lastňļ she declared, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I have certainly wronged my soul. Now I ňĻfullyňļ submit myself along with Solomon to Allah, the Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  27,45,"And We certainly sent to the people of Tham√Ľd their brother ŠĻĘ√ĘliŠł•, proclaiming, ‚ÄúWorship Allah,‚ÄĚ but they suddenly split into two opposing groups"
  27,46,"He urged ňĻthe disbelieving groupňļ, ‚ÄúO my people! Why do you ňĻseek toňļ hasten the torment¬†rather than grace?¬†If only you sought Allah‚Äôs forgiveness so you may be shown mercy!‚ÄĚ"
  27,47,"They replied, ‚ÄúYou and your followers are a bad omen for us.‚ÄĚ¬†He responded, ‚ÄúYour omens are destined by Allah. In fact, you are ňĻonlyňļ a people being tested.‚ÄĚ"
  27,48,"And there were in the city nine ňĻeliteňļ men who spread corruption in the land, never doing what is right"
  27,49,"They vowed, ‚ÄúLet us swear by Allah that we will take him and his family down by night. Then we will certainly say to his ňĻclosestňļ heirs, ‚ÄėWe did not witness the murder of his family. We are definitely telling the truth.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  27,50,"And ňĻsoňļ they made a plan, but We too made a plan, while they were unaware"
  27,51,"See then what the consequences of their plan were: We ňĻutterlyňļ destroyed them and their people all together"
  27,52,"So their homes are there, ňĻbut completelyňļ ruined because of their wrongdoing. Surely in this is a lesson for people of knowledge"
  27,53,And We delivered those who were faithful and were mindful ňĻof Allahňļ
  27,54,"And ňĻrememberňļ Lot, when he rebuked ňĻthe men ofňļ his people, ‚ÄúDo you commit that shameful deed while you can see ňĻone anotherňļ"
  27,55,"Do you really lust after men instead of women? In fact, you are ňĻonlyňļ a people acting ignorantly.‚ÄĚ"
  27,56,"But his people‚Äôs only response was to say, ‚ÄúExpel Lot‚Äôs followers from your land! They are a people who wish to remain chaste!‚ÄĚ"
  27,57,"So We delivered him and his family, except his wife. We had destined her to be one of the doomed"
  27,58,And We poured upon them a rain ňĻof brimstoneňļ. How evil was the rain of those who had been warned
  27,59,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúPraise be to Allah, and peace be upon the servants He has chosen.‚ÄĚ ňĻAsk the disbelievers,ňļ ‚ÄúWhich is better: Allah or whatever ňĻgodsňļ they associate ňĻwith Himňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  27,60,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho created the heavens and the earth, and sends down rain for you from the sky, by which We cause delightful gardens to grow? You could never cause their trees to grow. Was it another god besides Allah?‚ÄĚ Absolutely not! But they are a people who set up equals ňĻto Allahňļ"
  27,61,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho made the earth a place of settlement, caused rivers to flow through it, placed firm mountains upon it, and set a barrier between ňĻfresh and saltňļ bodies of water?¬†Was it another god besides Allah?‚ÄĚ Absolutely not! But most of them do not know"
  27,62,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho responds to the distressed when they cry to Him, relieving ňĻtheirňļ affliction, and ňĻWhoňļ makes you successors in the earth? Is it another god besides Allah? Yet you are hardly mindful!‚ÄĚ"
  27,63,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho guides you in the darkness of the land and sea,¬†and sends the winds ushering in His mercy?¬†Is it another god besides Allah? Exalted is Allah above what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ"
  27,64,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho originates the creation then resurrects it, and gives you provisions from the heavens and the earth? Is it another god besides Allah?‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúShow ňĻmeňļ your proof, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  27,65,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúNone in the heavens and the earth has knowledge of the unseen except Allah. Nor do they know when they will be resurrected"
  27,66,"No! Their knowledge of the Hereafter amounts to ignorance. In fact, they are in doubt about it. In truth, they are ňĻtotallyňļ blind to it"
  27,67,"The disbelievers ask, ‚ÄúWhen we and our fathers are reduced to dust, will we really be brought forth ňĻaliveňļ"
  27,68,"We have already been promised this, as well as our forefathers earlier. This is nothing but ancient fables!‚ÄĚ"
  27,69,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúTravel throughout the land and see the fate of the wicked.‚ÄĚ"
  27,70,"Do not grieve for them, nor be distressed by their schemes"
  27,71,"They ask ňĻthe believersňļ, ‚ÄúWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  27,72,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúPerhaps some of what you seek to hasten is close at hand.‚ÄĚ"
  27,73,"Surely your Lord is ever Bountiful to humanity,¬†but most of them are ungrateful"
  27,74,And surely your Lord knows what their hearts conceal and what they reveal
  27,75,For there is nothing hidden in the heavens or the earth without being ňĻwrittenňļ in a perfect Record
  27,76,"Indeed, this Quran clarifies for the Children of Israel most of what they differ over"
  27,77,And it is truly a guide and mercy for the believers
  27,78,"Your Lord will certainly judge between them by His justice, for He is the Almighty, All-Knowing"
  27,79,"So put your trust in Allah, for you are surely upon the ňĻPath ofňļ clear truth"
  27,80,You certainly cannot make the dead hear ňĻthe truthňļ. Nor can you make the deaf hear the call when they turn their backs and walk away
  27,81,"Nor can you lead the blind out of their misguidance. You can make none hear ňĻthe truthňļ except those who believe in Our revelations, ňĻfullyňļ submitting ňĻto Allahňļ"
  27,82,"And when the decree ňĻof the Hourňļ comes to pass against them, We will bring forth for them a beast from the earth,¬†telling them that the people had no sure faith in Our revelations"
  27,83,"ňĻWatch forňļ the Day We will gather from every faith-community a group of those who denied Our revelations, and they will be driven in ranks"
  27,84,"When they ňĻfinallyňļ come before their Lord, He will ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúDid you deny My revelations without ňĻevenňļ comprehending them? Or what ňĻexactlyňļ did you do?‚ÄĚ"
  27,85,"And the decree ňĻof tormentňļ will be justified against them for their wrongdoing, leaving them speechless"
  27,86,Do they not see that We made the night for them to rest in and the day bright?¬†Surely in this are signs for those who believe
  27,87,"And ňĻbeware ofňļ the Day the Trumpet will be blown, and all those in the heavens and all those on the earth will be horrified ňĻto the point of deathňļ,¬†except those Allah wills ňĻto spareňļ. And all will come before Him, fully humbled"
  27,88,"Now you see the mountains, thinking they are firmly fixed, but they are travelling ňĻjustňļ like clouds. ňĻThat isňļ the design of Allah, Who has perfected everything. Surely He is All-Aware of what you do"
  27,89,"Whoever comes with a good deed will be rewarded with what is better, and they will be secure from the horror on that Day"
  27,90,And whoever comes with an evil deed will be hurled face-first into the Fire. Are you rewarded except for what you used to do
  27,91,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI have only been commanded to worship the Lord of this city ňĻof Meccaňļ, Who has made it sacred, and to Him belongs everything. And I am commanded to be one of those who ňĻfullyňļ submit ňĻto Himňļ"
  27,92,"and to recite the Quran.‚ÄĚ Then whoever chooses to be guided, it is only for their own good. But whoever chooses to stray, say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI am only a warner.‚ÄĚ"
  27,93,"And say, ‚ÄúAll praise is for Allah! He will show you His signs, and you will recognize them. And your Lord is never unaware of what you do.‚ÄĚ"